{#
	Honeypot trap field — real visitors never see or fill this in; most
	bots auto-fill every field they find. Checked server-side (before the
	reCAPTCHA API call, so obvious bot traffic never costs a network
	round-trip) in modules/contactform/Module.php.

	Hidden off-canvas + aria-hidden/tabindex rather than display:none, so
	it stays invisible to screen reader and keyboard users too (some bots
	specifically skip display:none fields, off-canvas positioning avoids
	tipping them off).
#}
<div class="honeypot-field" aria-hidden="true" style="position:absolute; left:-9999px; width:1px; height:1px; overflow:hidden;">
	<label for="hpName">Leave this field blank</label>
	<input type="text" id="hpName" name="message[hpName]" tabindex="-1" autocomplete="off">
</div>
